content.text:
Let me help you solve this building block challenge by breaking down the analysis step by step:

1. Analyzing the Main Target Image:
- Total blocks: 9 blocks
- Layers: 3 layers
- Colors used: Orange (cylindrical and triangular), Yellow, Green, Blue
- Unique structure with cylindrical supports and rectangular/triangular blocks

2. Selecting Blocks from Dictionary:
Required blocks by index:
- Blue block (index 1): 1 piece
- Green blocks (index 3 and 5): 2 pieces
- Yellow blocks (index 6 and 8): 2 pieces
- Orange cylindrical blocks (index 10): 2 pieces
- Orange triangular blocks (index 14): 2 pieces

3. Assembly Instructions:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 3 (green base)
    Step2: Move block with index 10 (orange cylinder) on top of green base
    Step3: Move block with index 6 (yellow block) next to first orange cylinder
    Step4: Move block with index 5 (green block) on the other side of yellow block
    Step5: Move block with index 10 (second orange cylinder) on green block
    Step6: Move block with index 8 (yellow block) next to second orange cylinder
    Step7: Move block with index 1 (blue block) on top of yellow block
    Step8: Move block with index 14 (orange triangular block) on yellow block
    Step9: Move second block with index 14 (orange triangular block) on other structure
}
